{"id": "1447857128042926161", "channel_id": "1447553477638094898", "type": 19, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "ok, will try to get it later", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T07:47:19.210000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": ["1131790839291596841"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1447856964670460045", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447553477638094898", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Doresain targeting issue", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
{"id": "1447944509160947844", "channel_id": "1447553477638094898", "type": 19, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "This are examples of what we mean.\nDoresain exalt and most damaging cards can't ever hit the boss, particularly in the second phase that automatically spawn at turn start.\nAnd for jenkin or others that use random targeting, like Sorel, they can waste most or even all of the damage because they can target the totally immune mobs.\nIn a normal fight you can at least remove another enemy and get a kill effect if your damage don't go to the boss, but in this you just waste the damage, that is why we suggested to make the invulnerable dolls Not Targetable too.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:34:32.492000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-09T13:39:18.383000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": ["1131790839291596841"], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1447944506564415578", "filename": "2025-12-09_14-17-01.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 28505074, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1447553477638094898/1447944506564415578/2025-12-09_14-17-01.mp4?ex=69cbcd67&is=69ca7be7&hm=d0e2eb5d3da4b3087c4b76d5df7c804ea522b178c3f7bfb61199c5210287dc60&"}, {"id": "1447944507994931340", "filename": "2025-12-09_14-22-14.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 9851425, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1447553477638094898/1447944507994931340/2025-12-09_14-22-14.mp4?ex=69cbcd68&is=69ca7be8&hm=5097d517d9cec78c47cfae3e89d6a946fbb0b95657387c018f66a433e76800f7&"}, {"id": "1447944508896448622", "filename": "2025-12-09_14-23-49.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 7838193, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1447553477638094898/1447944508896448622/2025-12-09_14-23-49.mp4?ex=69cbcd68&is=69ca7be8&hm=ff083958496f4b942567bd064244ee0bb57ab4ddf32954598b3fe4e878e4ac2f&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": "1447856964670460045", "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447553477638094898", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Doresain targeting issue", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168893200044183"]}
{"id": "1448061490652254263", "channel_id": "1448061490652254263", "type": 0, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "In the current D-tide W3, and probably in general, if the mob dolls are already invulnerable when the boss Change Phase, they get the bonus STR a Second Time because they \"Die\" again during it, activating their Passive again.\nPls fix.", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T21:19:23.053000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": "2025-12-10T09:54:26.206000+00:00", "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [{"id": "1448061491902287943", "filename": "2025-12-09_22-07-40.mp4", "content_type": "video/mp4", "size": 10252821, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1448061490652254263/1448061491902287943/2025-12-09_22-07-40.mp4?ex=69cc3a5b&is=69cae8db&hm=d022761cfd06acf72b2ca38a6e956beb9abf37b3297cd19771b11c595e508200&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1448061490652254263", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "💭「Processing」Doll Boss STR bug", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168103141416960", "1361168893200044183"]}
{"id": "1447912791972511806", "channel_id": "1447912791972511806", "type": 0, "author_id": "1437487264023318668", "author_name": "vxvendetta97", "author_bot": false, "content": "So, different people, from en and cn, have already expressed that his naming archetype is not really in line with the game, and, for what I researched (you can prove me wrong if I'm mistaken), changing them should be pretty easy and work retroactively.\n\nThe names we could propose are Student > Senior > Investigator > Keeper (more intermediary can be added before Investigator if more titles are needed, but I don't think we need too much more than 5-6 at max).\nWhat do you think?", "timestamp": "2025-12-09T11:28:30.525000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "agree", "emoji_id": "1400771815076528258", "count": 5}], "attachments": [{"id": "1447912792454594630", "filename": "sdwwwq.JPG", "content_type": "image/jpeg", "size": 3049, "url": "https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/1447912791972511806/1447912792454594630/sdwwwq.JPG?ex=69cbafde&is=69ca5e5e&hm=a26ab808f6b160d9c15bd661aed04aa5d82314ff290e94ccd07774548a473c46&"}], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1447912791972511806", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Resolved」Name Changes for the bot Titles", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785"]}
